NMMES-TR in FY18 accomplished the following work increments: 
1) Completed the design and development of a Work Brokering solution. This solution addressed both public and private yards for ship maintenance requirements and ship class maintenance plans that are then screened into maintenance availability projects for individual platforms - and then brokered to a maintenance activity for accomplishment based on available capabilities; 
2) Conducted the design architecture, systems engineering, configuration and delivery of an Enterprise Services Bus (ESB) network/interfacing environment to provide for the support and transition from the NMMES solution to the NMMES-TR solution; 
3) Conducted the planning and preparation for the acquisition (including releasing a Request for Proposal), the configuration, and the deployment of a Maintenance, Repair, and Overhaul (MRO) replacement solution TR increment.  The schedule of this increment has been aligned with the Work Brokering solution and the ESB environment.
